<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12146h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12146h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12146h"> 146(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Celtic punishment / put him in a boat</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;on voyait d&eacute;ja et l&apos;on vit plus tard des hommes monter dans une barque, et, s&apos;abandonnant &agrave; la Providance, gagner des &icirc;les d&eacute;sertes o&ugrave; ils passaient le reste de leur vie. <br><font color="green">[19: Une sorte de ch&acirc;timent consistait &agrave; abandonner le condamn&eacute; dans une barque sans voile, ni rame.]</font> <br><font color="green">[We have already heard and we shall hear later, of men who entering a bark, and abandoning themselves to Providence, reached the shores of some desert island, there to spend the rest of their lives.]</font> <br><font color="green">[One form of punishment consisted in abandoning the condemned man in a boat with neither sail nor oar.]</font> <small> Riguet, Abb&eacute; <a name="RTSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RTSP"><cite title="source">Saint Patrice</cite></a> (1911) 157</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
